-- Orascom's Besix Venture Wins $265 Million Deal to Build Bahrain Causeway
-- Alaa Shahine
-- 2010-06-14T13:09:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/orascom-says-besix-venture-wins-265-million-bahrain-causeway-contract.html

          
          
             Orascom Construction Industries ,
Egypt’s biggest publicly traded builder, said today that Besix
Group has won a $265 million contract for the North Manama
causeway in Bahrain.  
 Besix won the contract as part of a joint venture with the
Haji Hassan Group, Cairo-based Orascom, which owns 50 percent of
Besix, said in a  statement  on its website.  
 Besix’s share of the contract is about $203 million,
Orascom, headed by Egyptian billionaire  Nassef Sawiris , said in
the statement. The project is scheduled for completion during
the second quarter of 2013, it said.  
 Shares of the company rose 0.6 percent to 226.8 Egyptian
pounds at the close in Cairo.  
 The project in Bahrain entails 2.42 kilometers of causeway
road on reclaimed land and 1.6 kilometers of existing road
reconstruction, the statement said.  
 It will provide road access to the Bahrain Financial Harbor
and Bahrain Business Bay, it added. Orascom provides
construction services in the Middle East, Africa, Asia and
Europe.  
